  <description type="morphology">Stems weakly julaceous. Leaves strongly imbricate when dry, flat to somewhat concave, 0.6–1.4 mm; costa percurrent to short-excurrent, mucro smooth; distal laminal cells elongate-rhomboidal, 40–60 µm, 6:1, walls not or weakly sinuate. Specialized asexual reproduction by leaf axil bulbils, red-brown, leafy, small. Seta 2–3 cm. Capsule erect or suberect, red, ovate-cylindric, 1–3 mm; peristome single, highly reduced, of unknown origin; endostome segments and cilia absent. Spores 8–15 µm.</description>
